# 📦 Backup Automation Script

## 📌 Objective

This project automates the process of creating compressed backups of a source directory using a Bash script.

---

## 🚀 Features

- Creates timestamped backups
- Compresses files into `.tar.gz`
- Checks if the source directory exists
- Reports success or failure using exit codes
- Stores backups in a dedicated `backups/` directory

---

## 🛠 Commands Practiced

- tar
- date
- if-else
- exit
- chmod
- mkdir
- echo
- Variables
- Command Substitution (`$(...)`)

---

## 📚 What I Learned

- Writing automation scripts in Bash
- Using variables and command substitution
- Creating compressed archives with `tar`
- Validating directory existence using `if [ -d ]`
- Understanding exit codes (`$?`)
- Handling script errors using `exit 1`

---

## ▶️ How to Run

```bash
chmod +x backup.sh
./backup.sh
```

